A number of leaders from across Africa are attending the funeral of Botswana's former president&nbsp;Sir Ketumile Masire. Botswana government said that among the dignitaries are His Majesty King Letsie of Lesotho and His Excellency President Robert Mugabe of Zimbabwe. Former South African president Thabo Mbeki is also attending the funeral. The former Botswana leader will be laid to rest today. Masire was the president of&nbsp;Botswana&nbsp;from 1980 to 1998. He died peacefully at Bokamoso Private Hospital last Thursday at the age of 91.